The paper deals with image steganalysis, which involves analyzing images to detect hidden messages. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The paper also discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for this task, which is a popular machine learning technique and falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper deals with the suppression of cover image content, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
